Package: fibr
Type: Package
Title: Prior-Fraction Diagnostics and Geometry-Guided Reparameterisation for
    Hierarchical MCMC
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Aidan D", "Bindoff",
           email   = "aidan.bindoff@utas.edu.au",
           role    = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0943-2702"))
Description: Tools for diagnosing and remedying the centring/non-centring
    obstruction in hierarchical Markov chain Monte Carlo, built on the fiber
    bundle structure of the joint parameter space. The Fisher information
    metric induces an Ehresmann connection on the base-fiber split; for the
    centred logistic GLMM this connection is flat, so the obstruction is not
    geometric holonomy but conditional dependence between base and fiber,
    governed per group by the prior fraction (the classical shrinkage or
    pooling factor). The package computes the analytic connection and prior
    fraction, estimates per-group loop-conditional dependence from a posterior
    chain, and supports per-group partial non-centring and connection-corrected
    proposals. The apparent 'holonomy' seen when the fiber is held fixed is a
    linearisation artifact. These pathologies are invisible to standard
    diagnostics such as R-hat, effective sample size, and divergence counts.
